r l BC-LEAH-PERSONALS-SFCHRO     09-12 0747
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LEAH-PERSONALS-SFCHRON </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 Copyright 1999 San Francisco Chronicle
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; THE BAY AREA'S BIGGEST BIG SHOTS &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Vanity Fair is out with its fifth ranking of the ``50 Most
Powerful Leaders of the Information Age,'' and once more,  &UR; Pee-wee &LR; 
 &UR; Herman &LR;  is not on the list. Never mind. Among the local lights:
</P>
<P>
   - No. 7 is  &UR; Steve Jobs  &LR; of Apple, who Vanity Fair says once
poured a glass of water on an employee's head during a meeting.
</P>
<P>
   - Tied for No. 11 are  &UR; Andrew Grove &LR;  and  &UR; Craig Barrett &LR;  of
Intel (who are the only Bay Area heavies about whom Vanity Fair
could find nothing at all of human interest or whimsy to report.)
</P>
<P>
   - No. 21 is occupied by  &UR; David Filo &LR; ,  &UR; Jerry Yang &LR;  and  &UR; Tim &LR; 
 &UR; Koogle &LR;  of Yahoo. Filo and Yang, sumo wrestling fans, are said to
have dressed in inflatable sumo customes and ``had it out in the
Yahoo parking lot.''
</P>
<P>
   - No. 29 is  &UR; John Doerr &LR; , a venture capitalist whose dinner
guests are often chilled. His home in Silicon Valley is a series of
freestanding pavilions between which guests scurry to and fro.
</P>
<P>
   - No. 30 is  &UR; Larry Ellison &LR;  of Oracle, who ``is plagued by a
well-deserved reputation as an irresponsible playboy.''
</P>
<P>
   - No. 31 is  &UR; Margaret Whitman &LR;  of eBay, who used to promote Mr.
Potato Head for Hasbro.
</P>
<P>
   - No. 34 is  &UR; Scott McNealy &LR;  of Sun Microsystems, who was
rejected by the San Francisco Golf Club, an ``old-money institution
that isn't very welcoming to brash new computer money.''
</P>
<P>
   - No. 42 is  &UR; George Lucas &LR; , who communicates daily with his
friend  &UR; Steven Spielberg &LR;  via a ``$3 million satellite-based
video-conferencing setup.''
</P>
<P>
   - No 46 is  &UR; Carleton Fiorina &LR;  of Hewlett-Packard, who ``showers
employees with flowers and balloons for exceptional performance.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; THOSE STALLONES &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Sylvester Stallone  &LR; told  &UR; Susan Faludi &LR; , who interviewed him
for her new book, ``Stiffed: The Betrayal of the Modern Man,'' that
his career is in the doldrums. ``I have not made a dime in two
years. I see everyone else working and I'm not doing d-. I'm in
total limbo. I'm a man without a country.''
</P>
<P>
   Stallone, whose comments were quoted in the New York Daily News,
told Faludi that Hollywood turned on him after he made ``Cop
Land.'' He said his agent,  &UR; Arnold Rifkind &LR; , ``sold me out,'' in
cahoots with Miramax's  &UR; Harvey Weinstein &LR; , who wanted him to make
more Rambo movies.
</P>
<P>
   ``I feel like the case of the Greek persona wearing the mask,''
he said of the macho roles he played before then. ``And he takes it
down, and you don't recognize who this person is. ... I don't
exist. It's like people see right through me.''
</P>
<P>
   P.S. &UR; Jacqueline Stallone &LR; , Sylvester's mom, told TV Guide Online
that she's augmented her astrology business with ``Rumpology,'' an
art she said she learned from a French woman. ``The crack of your
behind corresponds to the division of the two hemispheres of the
brain,'' she said. ``The buttocks represent areas of your
personality.'' Stallone said that the rump is divided into ``four
quadrants that correspond to the four elements: air, fire, water
and earth.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FLASH &LR;
</P>
<P>
   - A $500-a-person fund-raiser for  &UR; Willie Brown &LR;  is being hosted
on September 22 by his hatmaker,  &UR; Ruth Dewson &LR; , and his celebrity
pals  &UR; Danny Glover &LR; ,  &UR; Don Johnson &LR; ,  &UR; Terry McMillan &LR; ,
 &UR; Willie Mays &LR; ,  &UR; Nate Thurmond &LR;  and  &UR; Jerry Brown &LR;  (who sermonizes
against the evils of big-buck campaign fund raising).
</P>
<P>
   - In Israel, a memorial forest for  &UR; John F. Kennedy Jr. &LR; ,
 &UR; Carolyn Bessette Kennedy  &LR; and  &UR; Lauren Bessette &LR;  has been
established as part of the Kennedy Memorial Forest near Jerusalem.
More than 300 trees have been planted. The Jewish National Fund
also maintains memorial forests for  &UR; Ryan White &LR; ,
 &UR; John Lennon &LR; ,  &UR; Ingrid Bergman &LR;  and  &UR; Gene Siskel &LR; .
</P>
<P>
   - At a preview party in New York for ``The Minus Man,''
independent movie favorite  &UR; Sylvia Miles &LR; , 67, told  &UR; Baird Jones &LR; 
she was a finalist in the New York state chess championship at 16.
</P>
<P>
   - If you spent Saturday being aware of iguanas, you might have
noticed that the pinup featured here Friday was a meat-eating water
dragon, not a veggie iguana.
</P>
<P>
   -  &UR; Annette Bening  &LR; is eight weeks pregnant with Baby No. 4 by
 &UR; Warren Beatty &LR; .
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WHO SAID WHAT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &LR;   &LR; ``I've always believed that people have a right to know if
I'm a crook, but not if I'm a sinner, since we all are.''
</P>
<P>
   -  &UR; Bill Bradley &LR;  on WMUR in Manchester, N.H., quoted in Hotline.
</P>
