 (Eds.: Newspapers that used the Boston Globe story PBS-DONORS (w)
by Anne E. Kornblut, which moved Septl. 9, will wish to use the
following corrective.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   A Boston Globe article based on incorrect information in an
inspector general's report on fund raising by the Corporation for
Public Broadcasting erroneously stated that Maine PBS stations were
among those that swapped donor lists with political organizations.
The inspector general's office said Friday Maine stations did not
exchange or rent their lists.
</P>
