<HEADLINE>
A STRANGE DAY, BUT IT'S A VICTORY
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By RANDY GALLOWAY 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 
 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   LANDOVER, Md. _ |It was an overwhelming football afternoon,
which ended with a.MDBR/[.MDNM/ very.MDBR/].MDNM/ blurry, yet
.MDBR/ecstatic[ .MDNM/estastic.MDBR/].MDNM/ bottom line for the
Cowboys. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Over the course of nearly four hours, this team opened the 1999
season by being good, bad, ugly, losers, determined, gallant, and
finally.MDBR/ .MDNM/....MDBR/ .MDNM/a deserving winner. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Chan Gailey's postgame locker room speech to his club should
have been: &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``Guys, forget everything we did out there today, but remember
it forever.'' &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Yogi Berra would understand. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   If the Cowboys play like this every week, they won't win another
game. Either that, or they will go unbeaten for the season. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   This 41-35 overtime classic against the Redskins rewrote some
history, erased some longstanding myths, and maybe, just maybe,
proved a point to Michael Irvin. And also proved another point
about Irvin, not to mention Troy Aikman and Emmitt Smith. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``The best thing to me about everything today was watching us
.MDBR/be .MDNM/led by No. 8, No. 22 and No. 88,''.MDBR/[.MDNM/
said.MDBR/].MDNM/ Cowboys .MDBR/special teams[ .MDNM/specials'
team.MDBR/].MDNM/ coach Joe Avezzano.MDBR/ said.MDNM/. ``That kind
of took us back to our roots.'' &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Those, of course, are Super Bowl roots, which was another time
and another Cowboys' team, but.MDBR/ .MDNM/... &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Even in the glory days, the knock on Aikman was two-fold.
Doesn't throw a good deep ball and doesn't bring back the Cowboys
from Sunday afternoon scoreboard holes. Yesterday, Troy knocked
down two myths for the price of one Redskins Stadium ticket. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Down by 21 points to open the fourth quarter, Aikman whistled
three touchdown passes in a six-minute span, including overtime,
and for the final quarter and .MDBR/overtime[ .MDNM/OT.MDBR/].MDNM/
th.MDBR/r.MDNM/ew for 240 yards. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   And about that longstanding deep ball pox on Troy's football
house.MDBR/ _ .MDNM/he air-mailed a perfect strike to an open
Rocket Ismail, who never broke stride in catching.MDBR/[.MDNM/ what
would be.MDBR/].MDNM/ a 76-yard overtime TD bomb. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``I rejoice in a great victory for this football team,'' said
Aikman, ``but definitely not in trying to prove my critics wrong
about comebacks or deep balls or anything else. I am far past that
point in my career. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``And besides, those who have mistakenly believed that over the
years won't change their minds just because of today. For me, it's
only about trying to win football games.'' &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Which sound.MDBR/e.MDNM/d lik.MDBR/e.MDNM/ a postgame echo from
the other members of the Cowboys' Hall of Fame trifecta, meaning
Emmitt and yes, also Irvin, despite some earlier grumbling. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   It was a play-action fake to Emmitt on third-and-two in overtime
that baffled the Washington.MDBR/ .MDNM/defen.MDBR/s.MDNM/e. The
entire secondary took a run-stopping step forward. By then, Ismail
was blowing by them and Aikman was setting up at his .MDBR/own[
.MDNM/won.MDBR/].MDNM/ 20.MDBR/-.MDNM/yard line for the long
heave. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Emmitt getting the call seemed a natural on this critical
third-and-two from.MDBR/ .MDNM/the 2.MDBR/4.MDNM/. He already had
109 yards rushing. But Gailey fooled everyone with a
go-for-the-jugular bomb. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``To say I expected that play to be called at that point would
be lying,'' Aikman said. ``I thought we'd do what we do best.MDBR/
_ .MDNM/pound 'em .MDBR/\R.MDNM/with Emmitt.MDBR/\S.MDNM/. But when
the play came in, I'm thinking what a great call. I really thought
it'd work. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``Everybody is now praising Chan. But if it doesn't work, I
don't think you'd exactly be calling him creative,'' added Aikman,
laughing. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   On that point of Gailey's creativity, even many of his own
players were privately barking as the Cowboys fell behind by three
touchdowns in an awful third quarter. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The offense was stagnant, leaving Dave Campo's defense
overexposed, and a blowout Washington .MDBR/victory[
.MDNM/win.MDBR/].MDNM/ was brewing. Gailey's play calling appeared
to stray from basic bread-and-butter. Not enough running from
Emmitt, and Irvin was sitting out an entire series once, plus
various plays here and there. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't know if you'd call it mad..MDBR/ .MDNM/...MDBR/.
.MDNM/O.MDBR/K.MDNM/, you can call it mad,'' said Irvin, smiling.
``It's hard, difficult, different, not to be in there all the time.
But did it work today? Yes.'' &QL;
</P>
<P>
   .MDBR/Said Aikman: .MDNM/``Michael wasn't pleased, and in the
third quarter I also felt we were getting away from the run, which
didn't make the offensive line happy at all.MDBR/.[ .MDNM/,'' said
Aikman. ``.MDBR/] .MDNM/But then it started to all come together.
We got back to the run, and got Michael going.'' &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Gailey matter-of-factly explained, ``I'm going to be mixing it
up in every game, and if it appears we stray from the run at times,
hopefully it will set up the run for later. Which it did
t.MDBR/o.MDNM/day. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``With Michael, I personally heard no complaints, but I'd like
to think by resting him, it led to his great finish. When he made
the two late TD catches .MDBR/\R.MDNM/in the fourth
quarter.MDBR/\S.MDNM/, he sure looked fresh to me.'' Touche. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   By doubling his TD catches from last season, Irvin
immediate.MDBR/l.MDNM/y left behind that stigma of faded
superstar. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   It was a strange kind of victory, yet over the long afternoon,
some questions were answered and stigmas were crushed on several
fronts. ``Plus, winning sure beats the alternative,'' Aikman said. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Just ask any of the Redskins. &QL; 
