   NBC-ALONE (Undated) _ In the wake of Viacom's
multimillion-dollar betrothal to CBS, the media spotlight has swung
around to NBC, the last network unwed to a movie studio and left to
stand alone on the crowded, vertically integrated television dance
floor. But far from being jealous, NBC executives said they looked
at that transaction as an excellent asset match for the companies
involved _ but something of an irrelevance for themselves, because
it was simply not a deal that NBC could ever have made. By Bill
Carter.
