<P>
   BELLATLANTIC-VODAFONE (Undated) _ The British wireless giant
Vodafone Airtouch and the Bell Atlantic Corp., hostile adversaries
in January, are poised to become best friends in a venture that
would consolidate the two companies' U.S. cellular telephone
operations into a separate company valued between $70 billion and
$80 billion, according to people close to the talks. Although
executives for both companies cautioned Sunday that the
negotiations could still break down, as their advisers continued to
hash out details, the companies' boards were expected to meet in
the next few days to consider the deal in earnest. By Laura M.
Holson.
</P>
